ce:section.ce:para:
According to the size development direction of CQDs implementation materials, the synthesis methods are classified into two groups, including the "top-down" and "bottom-up" methods (Fig. 1
                     ). The top-down method generally uses graphite, activated carbon, and carbon nanotubes as raw materials to synthesise CQDs by arc discharge [26], laser ablation [27–29], electrochemical oxidation [30–33], chemical oxidation [34–37], hydrothermal decomposition [38,39] and ultrasonic treatment [40,41]. The bottom-up method generally uses citric acid, sucrose, glucose and other raw materials to synthesise CQDs by microwave method [42–44], template method [45], hydrothermal synthesis method and thermal decomposition [46,47]. Here, we introduce in detail several prominent methods for the preparation of CQDs. The comparison of the advantages and disadvantages of the methods are listed in Table 1
                     .
